<h1> Cowboy Bebop </h1>
<img src="..//mtrls/Cowboy_Bebop.png" width="800" height="450" alt="Cowboy_Bebop">

<h3><p>Cowboy Bebop (Japanese: カウボーイビバップ) is a Japanese neo-noir science fiction anime television series
    created and animated by Sunrise, led by a production team of director Shinichirō Watanabe, screenwriter Keiko Nobumoto, character designer Toshihiro Kawamoto. The series, which ran for twenty-six episodes, is set in the year 2071, and follows the lives of a traveling bounty-hunting crew aboard a spaceship, the Bebop. Although it incorporates a wide variety of genres, the series draws most heavily from science fiction, western, and noir films. Its most prominent themes are existential ennui, loneliness, and the inability to escape one's past.</p>

<h2> <em>Genres and one of the best anime of all time.</em> </h2></h3>

<h3><p>The genres are described as space opera meets noir, meets comedy, meets cyberpunk. </p>
    <p>It has also been described as a "genre-busting space western".</p></h3>
<h3><p>Cowboy Bebop has gained widespread critical and commercial success both in Japan and internationally. The series has won numerous awards in the field of animation and science fiction
    and has been recognized for its style, characters, plot, dubbing, animation, and soundtrack. Over the years the series has unfolded as a masterpiece of Japanese animation, and many critics consider it one of the best anime of all time.
<strong> Cowboy Bebop is one of the most original, entertaining programs where the overall concept is excellent, the characters are intriguing and the action is fantastic.</strong></p></h3>
<h2><em>Storyline</em></h2>
<h3><p><strong>Cowboy Bebop</strong> "Cowboy Bebop" tells the multifaceted story of people living on a spaceship called "Bebop. The name of the spaceship comes from the musical movement bebop. Bebop is the progenitor of modern jazz. Jett Black, a former police detective and owner of this ship,
    and Spike Spiegel, a man with a dark past, are partners who travel together and live what they earn from the bounty hunting profession that has become commonplace.</p>
    <p> They had absolutely no plans to increase the crew of the Bebop,
    which serves as their home and means of transportation. But the nets they cast to catch high-priced criminals and the dregs of society have brought them Faye Valentine, a woman with a mysterious past and a card player with a colossal debt, Ed, a lost eccentric girl and genius hacker, and Ayn, supposedly the smartest dog in the world.
    It is with this composition that the crew of the Bebop continues the business of bounty hunting. Their adventures are comic, ironic, philosophical, dramatic, as well as tragic. </p>
</h3>
